  "text": "The lysS gene from M. avium is 81% homologous to the lysX gene from M. tuberculosis. LysX from M. tuberculosis is required for synthesis of lysinylated phosphatidylglycerol. A LysX mutant was shown to be sensitive to cationic antibiotics and peptides, to be more lysosomeassociated and to display defective growth in mouse and guinea pig lungs [CITATION_1] .",
